  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ivwa Sustainable Agriculture and Livestock Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This four-year project will address the needs of the members of Organization of Peasants for the Development of the Eighth Section of Arcahaie in soil conservation, agroforestry, livestock management, and forage production. The project will improve the agricultural production of 2,024 participant families and the natural environment of the Eighth Section, where the organization is located. Over the four years, the project participants will implement 20 community nurseries and plant 250,000 fruit and forestry trees; promote grafting of fruit tree species including grapefruit, lemon, and avocado; distribute 54 goats, 10 pure-bred bulls and 600 poultry; distribute forage seeds and cuttings in 20 farm communities; and train and update the skills of 70 agricultural volunteers, which will be used to help farmers in further activities of the project. In addition, the 2024 participant families will pass on livestock, forage species and knowledge to the rest of the association to ensure project sustainability.</narrative>
  </description>
